15 disease are at an increased risk for accidental injury, getting lost or disoriented, and being
16 abused, neglected, and exploited; and
17 WHEREAS, caregivers for individuals with Alzheimer's disease and related dementias
18 experience a significant toll on their physical, mental, and financial health and often report
19 high levels of stress, anxiety, depression, and health problems; and
20 WHEREAS, there is an economic impact of Alzheimer's disease upon the business, medical,
21 and caregiver communities of Georgia; and
22 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this day be committed to increasing
23 awareness of Alzheimer's disease and other dementias to address the needs of this growing
24 segment of Georgia's population.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
26 recognize February 6, 2025, as Alzheimer's Awareness Day at the state capitol.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
28 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the public and the
29 press.
